name: Presumption that rule of law continues unchanged Rules of Court Applicability of District Court Rules of Civil Procedure, see DCRCP rule 81(b)(5).
text: Presumption that rule of law continues unchanged.  Unless a change in law has clearly been made, the provisions of the new U.C.C. shall be deemed declaratory of the meaning of the old U.C.C. [L 1978, c 155, pt of §1(34)]
